FBIS3-11939 "drlat060_a_94006" FBIS-LAT-93-060 Document Type:Daily Report 27 Mar 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Chilean Official Notes Increasing Economic Ties FL2703212294 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2030 GMT 27 Mar 94 FL2703212294 Havana Radio Reloj Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Cuban Consul General to Chile Humberto Hernandez has stressed the development of mutual economic and commercial ties between Cuba and Chile, notwithstanding the lack of full diplomatic relations. In an interview granted to the Chilean newspaper LA EPOCA, Hernandez said that since the restoration of consular ties two years ago, Chilean businessmen have expressed increasing interest in investing capital in the Caribbean island. The Cuban consul to Chile explained that Chileans are already investing in citrus production and that there are good prospects for tourism and companies to supply various products to the Caribbean nation. Concerning the reestablishment of full diplomatic ties at ambassadorial level, Hernandez insisted that the Cuban Government maintains a stance of absolute patience, waiting for the Chileans to take the first step.
